1
00:00:04,546 --> 00:00:06,298
THE FOLLOWING CONTENT CONTAINS DEPICTIONS
OF DOMESTIC ABUSE.

2
00:00:06,381 --> 00:00:07,466
VIEWER DISCRETION IS ADVISED.

3
00:00:12,012 --> 00:00:13,222
Aren't you tired? Huh?

4
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,265
Why don't you come sit down?

5
00:00:15,349 --> 00:00:16,934
Let's talk a little
and figure this out.

6
00:00:20,771 --> 00:00:24,024
If you give me the gold bar
and the knife, we can talk.

7
00:00:24,107 --> 00:00:25,651
Ugh, you're being really annoying.

8
00:00:33,492 --> 00:00:35,244
Closer.

9
00:00:39,790 --> 00:00:40,791
And the knife.

10
00:00:58,141 --> 00:01:01,520
You need to think about this
from an economic perspective, okay?

11
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:04,398
It really doesn't matter
if it's gold or drugs.

12
00:01:04,481 --> 00:01:07,192
All that matters
is raking in the dough.

13
00:01:07,276 --> 00:01:09,194
Can we turn that item into money or not?

14
00:01:09,278 --> 00:01:12,531
You really think taking the gold bar
to a jewelry shop's a good idea?

15
00:01:12,614 --> 00:01:14,992
A 10-kilogram bar
with a foreign stamp on it?

16
00:01:16,535 --> 00:01:18,453
Okay, just listen.

17
00:01:18,537 --> 00:01:22,040
The jewelry shops, the pawn shops even,
they're all linked to who I work for.

18
00:01:22,124 --> 00:01:24,918
Stuff like gold bars,
that's gonna get around.

19
00:01:25,002 --> 00:01:27,212
You wanna sell a gold bar,
you gotta hand over your phone number,

20
00:01:27,296 --> 00:01:29,131
name, and ID.
So what?

21
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:31,341
You'll write down,
"Kim Heeju, ID 123?"

22
00:01:31,425 --> 00:01:34,511
You think you can handle all this alone?
You can't.

23
00:01:34,595 --> 00:01:36,430
But I can.
I'm telling you.

24
00:01:36,513 --> 00:01:37,848
My methods are solid.

25
00:01:41,059 --> 00:01:42,436
How do we do it, then?

26
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:44,730
You a bit more interested now?

27
00:01:44,813 --> 00:01:48,233
Okay, before I lay all this out,
let's make a deal.

28
00:01:48,317 --> 00:01:50,277
-Hey, get back!
-Like partners.

29
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:52,029
I said get back. Go.

30
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:53,363
Talk from there.

31
00:02:02,164 --> 00:02:04,791
Okay, first, where's the casket?

32
00:02:04,875 --> 00:02:06,668
This can't be everything.

33
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:09,004
Just tell me where it is.

34
00:02:09,087 --> 00:02:10,839
I need to know exactly
how many bars there are

35
00:02:10,922 --> 00:02:12,007
before I can put a plan together.

36
00:02:12,090 --> 00:02:14,051
Why should I even trust you?

37
00:02:15,344 --> 00:02:16,845
I literally just told you!

38
00:02:17,679 --> 00:02:19,890
If I was gonna rat you out to the boss,
I would have done it already,

39
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:21,141
and all the guys would be here.

40
00:02:23,644 --> 00:02:26,480
Fine, I wasn't gonna tell you this.
Guess I have to, though.

41
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:29,358
Look.

42
00:02:29,441 --> 00:02:32,110
That shit hurt.
It still hurts.

43
00:02:32,903 --> 00:02:35,614
They were gonna cut off my ear
if I didn't start talking.

44
00:02:35,697 --> 00:02:37,074
But I held out.

45
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:40,160
You know why?
'Cause I thought of you.

46
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:41,828
What the hell?

47
00:02:41,912 --> 00:02:43,622
Why am I such a softie?

48
00:02:43,705 --> 00:02:45,248
Don't make me laugh.

49
00:02:45,332 --> 00:02:48,251
The only reason you showed up here
was to look for the drugs.

50
00:02:48,335 --> 00:02:50,170
If you couldn't find them
you would have threatened me

51
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:52,214
or done whatever it took
to make me talk.

52
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:54,216
And once you found them,
you would have killed me.

53
00:02:54,299 --> 00:02:56,343
Oh, really?
Correct me if I'm wrong here,

54
00:02:56,426 --> 00:02:58,762
but you were the one threatening
to shoot me.

55
00:03:00,597 --> 00:03:03,058
Okay, I get it.
Let's move on.

56
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:05,060
How about this?

57
00:03:05,143 --> 00:03:06,978
Don't tell me where to find the gold.

58
00:03:07,062 --> 00:03:08,480
I won't ask, either.

59
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:10,148
If you think I'd kill you

60
00:03:10,232 --> 00:03:13,318
and make a run for it after finding out
where the gold is, don't tell me.

61
00:03:13,402 --> 00:03:15,362
If I have no idea,
there's no problem, right?

62
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:16,988
Instead, how's this?

63
00:03:18,115 --> 00:03:20,325
Every three days,
you give me one gold bar.

64
00:03:20,409 --> 00:03:23,662
Then it'll be up to me
to sell it and bring you the cash.

65
00:03:23,745 --> 00:03:25,580
That means I won't be able
to pull anything funny

66
00:03:25,664 --> 00:03:26,748
until we've sold all the gold.

67
00:03:26,832 --> 00:03:27,916
Make sense?

68
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:30,919
How many are there?

69
00:03:31,002 --> 00:03:32,504
That I need to know.

70
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:38,760
There's ten.

71
00:03:44,599 --> 00:03:45,684
Ten?

72
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:50,105
If we sell one for a billion,
times ten is ten billion.

73
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:51,273
Split it in half.

74
00:03:51,356 --> 00:03:52,524
-Five billion each.
-Split it?

75
00:03:54,734 --> 00:03:56,695
You think it's just you and me?

76
00:03:56,778 --> 00:03:59,781
It's not our gold.
It belongs to Dokyung.

77
00:03:59,865 --> 00:04:00,991
What? Lee Dokyung?

78
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:02,617
Nah, he's gonna die soon.

79
00:04:02,701 --> 00:04:05,203
And even if he lives,
he's going to jail anyway.

80
00:04:05,287 --> 00:04:07,080
Wait, why not just cut him out?

81
00:04:07,164 --> 00:04:08,540
What'd you say?

82
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:10,792
Oh.

83
00:04:12,002 --> 00:04:13,003
What, are you dating?

84
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:16,131
Am I right?
Is he your boyfriend?

85
00:04:16,214 --> 00:04:18,300
Eh, doesn't matter.

86
00:04:18,383 --> 00:04:20,051
How is it Lee Dokyung's?

87
00:04:20,135 --> 00:04:21,553
You realize he stole it, right?

88
00:04:21,636 --> 00:04:23,221
So it really belongs to Chairman An.

89
00:04:23,972 --> 00:04:25,056
Okay, then.

90
00:04:26,850 --> 00:04:28,977
So the three of us will split it.

91
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:30,854
You'll get exactly one-third of the money.

92
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:32,105
That's your share.

93
00:04:33,315 --> 00:04:34,316
Okay.

94
00:04:34,858 --> 00:04:35,859
Okay!

95
00:04:38,403 --> 00:04:40,530
-So, then.
-What?

96
00:04:40,614 --> 00:04:42,866
-We should fist bump so that...
-Don't come any closer!

97
00:04:42,949 --> 00:04:45,243
Well, we gotta lock in our contract, so...

98
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:47,746
...fist bump to seal the deal.

99
00:04:49,247 --> 00:04:51,792
First you have to tell me how you plan
on selling the gold bars.

100
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,710
Explain that.
Then I'll decide.

101
00:04:53,794 --> 00:04:55,253
Are you serious?

102
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:57,297
What the...

103
00:04:58,423 --> 00:05:00,509
Fine. Listen carefully.

104
00:05:00,592 --> 00:05:04,930
Gold is traded in hundreds
of forms in shops across the country.

105
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:07,682
Gold rings, gold pigs, random stuff.

106
00:05:07,766 --> 00:05:09,768
And the gold bar.

107
00:05:09,851 --> 00:05:14,356
The one-kilogram bars are the easiest ones
for us to trade.

108
00:05:14,439 --> 00:05:18,318
Everything changes depending on
the weight, purity,

109
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:19,778
and where it was manufactured.

110
00:05:19,861 --> 00:05:23,782
So first we gotta break these down
into one-kilo bars

111
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:25,450
-and recast them.
-Who can do that?

112
00:05:26,368 --> 00:05:28,370
-You?
-No.

113
00:05:28,453 --> 00:05:30,622
We'll obviously need a goldsmith for that.

114
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:32,624
Then there's the actual sale.

115
00:05:32,707 --> 00:05:35,168
Selling a 10-kilo bar would be hard,

116
00:05:35,252 --> 00:05:36,837
but small ones, well,

117
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:39,005
jewelry stores have
no problem buying those.

118
00:05:39,923 --> 00:05:43,134
All of Gwangwon-do has ties to our company
so that won't work.

119
00:05:43,218 --> 00:05:45,303
I'll have to go to jewelry stores
in other areas

120
00:05:45,387 --> 00:05:47,639
and sell only one bar per store.

121
00:05:47,722 --> 00:05:50,016
The whole process of recasting
a bar to selling it

122
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:53,311
shouldn't take any more than, say,
three days.

123
00:05:53,395 --> 00:05:55,939
So selling them all should take a month.

124
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:57,816
And to avoid being tracked by the cops,

125
00:05:57,899 --> 00:06:00,277
we gotta make all
of our transactions in cash.

126
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:03,530
Not to mention, we'll need fake IDs,
burner phones, and burner bank accounts.

127
00:06:03,613 --> 00:06:07,033
But I'll be taking care of all that,
so don't you worry about a thing.

128
00:06:07,117 --> 00:06:08,785
SAMJIN GOLD EXCHANGE

129
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:15,125
And Heeju,
let's make one thing clear.

130
00:06:16,918 --> 00:06:19,212
Until we've sold all ten gold bars
and split the cash,

131
00:06:19,296 --> 00:06:20,714
we trust each other.

132
00:06:22,757 --> 00:06:26,052
Never, seriously never...

133
00:06:27,012 --> 00:06:30,390
Ever, ever, ever,
never betray each other.

134
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:32,893
Do you promise?
If not, we're both dead.

135
00:06:33,852 --> 00:06:36,730
You'll be discovered in that mining town
hanging from your neck.

136
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:38,607
And as for me,
I'm screwing the company over, too,

137
00:06:38,690 --> 00:06:42,319
so I'll get something chopped off
and become a cripple.

138
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:46,323
You know what I'm saying?

139
00:06:50,577 --> 00:06:52,329
You're the one I'm worried about.

140
00:06:58,209 --> 00:06:59,711
Okay.

141
00:07:03,548 --> 00:07:04,966
Do this to sign the contract.

142
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:07,218
Hmm? Deal?

143
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:15,602
You gotta say "deal" when you do it.
That's how it works.

144
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:17,020
Deal.

145
00:07:21,858 --> 00:07:22,859
Deal.

146
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:30,116
Finally.

147
00:08:16,538 --> 00:08:21,251
EPISODE 3
PARTNERSHIP

148
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:22,335
Yeah.

149
00:08:27,424 --> 00:08:29,884
Goodness.

150
00:08:39,811 --> 00:08:41,896
Careful.
Ugh, shit.

151
00:08:44,566 --> 00:08:46,067
SEOYOON, YERIN, I'M SORRY FOR GOING FIRST.
TO EVERYONE WHO WAS HARMED BECAUSE OF ME,

152
00:08:46,151 --> 00:08:47,610
I AM SORRY. THIS IS THE LAST CHOICE
I CAN MAKE. I'M SORRY. I'M SO SORRY.

153
00:08:49,237 --> 00:08:50,238
Hold up. Stop.

154
00:09:04,961 --> 00:09:06,087
Go, yeah.

155
00:09:08,173 --> 00:09:09,257
Should I send him to forensics?

156
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:10,717
Nah, just the morgue is fine.

157
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:11,885
-Yes, sir.
-Yeah.

158
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:13,303
The morgue.

159
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:21,311
-Take him to the morgue.
-Understood.

160
00:09:28,693 --> 00:09:30,779
Ah, I did it. Yeah.

161
00:09:30,862 --> 00:09:32,989
I took care of it like you asked.

162
00:09:33,073 --> 00:09:34,783
Who wrote that note, though?

163
00:09:35,992 --> 00:09:37,786
Looked like President Go's handwriting.

164
00:09:39,788 --> 00:09:41,831
You gotta stop with all
these useless theatrics.

165
00:09:41,915 --> 00:09:44,334
It's a waste.
Just keep your guys in line.

166
00:09:45,460 --> 00:09:46,544
Thanks for your work.

167
00:09:47,712 --> 00:09:49,297
See you soon, Detective.

168
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:50,423
Sounds good.

169
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:55,178
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL

170
00:10:07,565 --> 00:10:09,359
What the hell have we been doing all day?

171
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:11,945
We left the shop unattended.

172
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:13,321
Ms. Yeo Sunok.

173
00:10:13,404 --> 00:10:15,240
Here. Come on.

174
00:10:24,499 --> 00:10:25,792
Hello.

175
00:10:25,875 --> 00:10:27,335
Could the patient wait outside?

176
00:10:27,418 --> 00:10:29,170
I'd like to speak with the guardian first.

177
00:10:29,254 --> 00:10:32,006
-Uh...
-You can just talk.

178
00:10:32,090 --> 00:10:33,591
I already know anyway.

179
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:41,558
You were diagnosed here a year ago,
but you never went to another hospital?

180
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:43,351
No.

181
00:10:43,434 --> 00:10:45,270
We should
have started treatment then.

182
00:10:45,353 --> 00:10:46,813
We're a little late now.

183
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:48,940
If you look here,

184
00:10:49,023 --> 00:10:52,235
you'll see that the tumor cells
have metastasized to the lungs.

185
00:10:53,611 --> 00:10:56,614
Were you feeling okay?
I imagine the pain would be quite severe.

186
00:10:57,866 --> 00:11:00,076
Could surgery be an option?

187
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,911
She should get hospitalized first.

188
00:11:02,662 --> 00:11:04,122
I recommend an examination,

189
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:06,666
then beginning chemotherapy
to slow down the metastasis.

190
00:11:06,749 --> 00:11:08,835
As for surgery,

191
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:11,212
let's see how things progress
and then decide.

192
00:11:11,796 --> 00:11:14,465
-'Kay.
-So my cancer's in the final stage.

193
00:11:14,549 --> 00:11:16,259
Wouldn't surgery be useless?

194
00:11:16,342 --> 00:11:19,053
Well, when it comes to stages,

195
00:11:19,137 --> 00:11:20,221
you could say that, however...

196
00:11:20,305 --> 00:11:21,431
How much longer do I have?

197
00:11:21,514 --> 00:11:24,642
A specific time frame
is hard to determine at this point.

198
00:11:24,726 --> 00:11:26,686
If I get treatment, I can live...

199
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:28,605
...how much longer?
Into my 80s?

200
00:11:28,688 --> 00:11:31,566
-Auntie.
-I knew it'd be like this.

201
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:33,151
They wanna fill me with drugs...

202
00:11:33,818 --> 00:11:36,196
...and poke me with needles even though
I'm dying anyway.

203
00:11:36,279 --> 00:11:39,574
That's how hospitals make money, isn't it?
Hey, we're leaving.

204
00:11:39,657 --> 00:11:40,909
-Auntie!
-Get up. I'm done with all this.

205
00:11:40,992 --> 00:11:42,869
Auntie, please wait! Seriously!

206
00:11:46,664 --> 00:11:48,791
-Auntie.
-Just forget it.

207
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:51,127
Oh, come on, please!

208
00:11:51,211 --> 00:11:52,629
I said forget it!

209
00:11:52,712 --> 00:11:54,464
These guys are all crooks.

210
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:56,382
They don't deserve our hard-earned money.

211
00:11:56,466 --> 00:11:59,010
If this is really about the money,
don't worry.

212
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:00,803
-I have it.
-Where? Show me.

213
00:12:00,887 --> 00:12:02,388
I wanna see some before I die.

214
00:12:06,726 --> 00:12:08,478
Aren't you in a lot of pain right now?

215
00:12:09,187 --> 00:12:11,689
This is about more than
just you living longer.

216
00:12:11,773 --> 00:12:13,775
Come on.
You're not dead yet.

217
00:12:13,858 --> 00:12:16,945
At least let them give you something
to ease the pain while you're still alive.

218
00:12:18,363 --> 00:12:20,156
Since when did you worry
about me like this?

219
00:12:21,616 --> 00:12:23,159
You were the one who ran off
to live your own life.

220
00:12:25,453 --> 00:12:28,998
And now that I'm dying,
you suddenly have a sense of duty?

221
00:12:29,082 --> 00:12:31,626
You're the one who needs to have
a sense of duty.

222
00:12:31,709 --> 00:12:35,213
What kind of mother wants to just die
and leave their kid by themself?

223
00:12:37,382 --> 00:12:38,675
Am I your mother?

224
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:40,551
Well, aren't you?

225
00:12:41,386 --> 00:12:43,554
You gave birth to me.

226
00:12:48,351 --> 00:12:49,978
You think I had you
'cause I wanted to?

227
00:13:43,656 --> 00:13:49,579
WELCOME TO GOLD LAND
THE CITY OF DREAMS AND HOPES

228
00:13:56,878 --> 00:13:57,879
Hey.

229
00:14:01,132 --> 00:14:03,342
Yeah...

230
00:14:04,010 --> 00:14:07,180
What's this?
I expected a nice spread.

231
00:14:07,263 --> 00:14:10,141
Ah, come on.
Guess not.

232
00:14:10,224 --> 00:14:11,976
So disappointing.

233
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:16,230
Anyway, I guess the chairman
isn't back from overseas.

234
00:14:17,273 --> 00:14:18,483
I must say, you're looking great.

235
00:14:19,817 --> 00:14:21,611
It must be fun playing
the chairman.

236
00:14:21,694 --> 00:14:23,404
Lee Dokyung's cell phone.

237
00:14:23,488 --> 00:14:25,114
Same guy you were tracking
a few days ago.

238
00:14:25,198 --> 00:14:27,492
-Does that mean he's dead?
-No, he's in the hospital.

239
00:14:27,575 --> 00:14:29,577
But now the cops are on his tail.

240
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:31,287
Hence our little meeting here.

241
00:14:31,370 --> 00:14:34,207
Not much I can do.
Not if the police are on him. No way.

242
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:36,042
I'm not asking you to do anything
to Lee Dokyung.

243
00:14:37,668 --> 00:14:40,963
Just take this phone
and use it to find a person.

244
00:14:43,216 --> 00:14:45,051
No way he's working alone.

245
00:14:46,219 --> 00:14:47,220
He's got an accomplice.

246
00:14:48,179 --> 00:14:51,891
A stupid fuck who took off with
the van carrying all of our stuff.

247
00:14:53,976 --> 00:14:55,436
Ah, the casket.

248
00:14:56,312 --> 00:14:57,814
Ah, that must be a headache.

249
00:14:58,815 --> 00:15:02,527
Just dig through his calls and texts
and see what you can find.

250
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:05,571
You can't expect me to do all that.
Come on.

251
00:15:05,655 --> 00:15:07,990
Searching through
a phone like that's illegal.

252
00:15:08,074 --> 00:15:09,534
And it takes too much time.

253
00:15:10,743 --> 00:15:13,037
Too much money, too.

254
00:15:13,121 --> 00:15:14,622
I'll give you the money,
so don't worry.

255
00:15:14,705 --> 00:15:15,873
Oh, yeah.

256
00:15:15,957 --> 00:15:17,333
Let me think about it, okay?

257
00:15:18,501 --> 00:15:19,710
There's no time for thinking.

258
00:15:20,878 --> 00:15:22,755
I gotta do this before
the chairman returns.

259
00:15:22,839 --> 00:15:24,590
And when is that?

260
00:15:25,633 --> 00:15:27,677
At the end of the month.

261
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,095
I am curious, though.

262
00:15:29,804 --> 00:15:30,847
What's in the casket?

263
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:32,557
Do you know?

264
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:35,560
Drugs? Meth?

265
00:15:36,394 --> 00:15:37,728
Organs?

266
00:15:37,812 --> 00:15:40,940
Ah, you gangster assholes keep getting
into organ trafficking these days.

267
00:15:41,023 --> 00:15:42,024
You just can't help yourselves.

268
00:15:42,108 --> 00:15:43,818
Why the fuck do you need
to know everything?

269
00:15:45,069 --> 00:15:46,445
Just do what you usually do.

270
00:15:47,405 --> 00:15:49,157
Do what I'm telling you.

271
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:54,871
Ah, hold on.

272
00:15:57,832 --> 00:16:01,878
Do I look like the kind of guy who
just does whatever you tell him to?

273
00:16:04,255 --> 00:16:05,798
Of course I'm that guy.

274
00:16:06,716 --> 00:16:07,717
Right.

275
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:11,470
Fine, fine, I'll do it.

276
00:16:11,554 --> 00:16:12,555
Huh?

277
00:16:15,349 --> 00:16:17,852
Ah, dammit.

278
00:16:17,935 --> 00:16:20,855
GANGWON CENTRAL POLICE AGENCY

279
00:16:26,569 --> 00:16:29,238
Oh. Oh, there you are.

280
00:16:30,865 --> 00:16:32,658
-Here.
-Yeah.

281
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:40,416
Read it, then shred it.

282
00:16:40,499 --> 00:16:42,960
You leave that lying around,
you'll get audited or somethin'.

283
00:16:43,044 --> 00:16:47,006
Oh. You think you're all that just 'cause
you're stationed at headquarters now?

284
00:16:48,716 --> 00:16:50,009
I'm your senior.

285
00:16:51,093 --> 00:16:52,053
ON-SITE INVESTIGATION REPORT

286
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:53,137
It's a burner car.

287
00:16:53,221 --> 00:16:54,555
The plate number is fake, too.

288
00:16:54,639 --> 00:16:56,015
Dash cam?

289
00:16:56,098 --> 00:16:57,099
Nothin'.

290
00:16:57,183 --> 00:16:58,893
No surveillance cams in the area, either.

291
00:16:58,976 --> 00:17:00,353
So we don't know who the driver is.

292
00:17:01,729 --> 00:17:02,730
Why?

293
00:17:03,731 --> 00:17:04,982
The casket?

294
00:17:05,066 --> 00:17:06,484
Those Geumseong guys didn't take it?

295
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:08,194
I don't think so.

296
00:17:08,277 --> 00:17:09,528
What does that mean?

297
00:17:09,612 --> 00:17:10,863
They either took it or they didn't.

298
00:17:10,947 --> 00:17:12,823
So why do you need all this?

299
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:16,077
To keep Lee Dokyung quiet
in case he wants to talk?

300
00:17:16,786 --> 00:17:19,497
-Maybe.
-Uh, wait a minute.

301
00:17:20,081 --> 00:17:22,083
I'm not gonna be party to a murder.

302
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:23,918
If that's the plan then I'm done.

303
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:25,544
This is the last time I'm helping.

304
00:17:25,628 --> 00:17:27,880
You can tell Park
I'm not doing this anymore.

305
00:17:27,964 --> 00:17:31,092
And doing this will pay off my debts.

306
00:17:33,761 --> 00:17:34,762
Hey.

307
00:17:36,097 --> 00:17:37,723
How big of a hole are you in?

308
00:17:37,807 --> 00:17:39,684
100 million won?

309
00:17:40,643 --> 00:17:43,980
Oh, man, you really poured it down
the drain, didn't you?

310
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:48,776
What do you like to play?
Baccarat?

311
00:17:49,694 --> 00:17:51,904
Ah, it won't be easy
to climb outta that hole.

312
00:17:54,657 --> 00:17:55,700
What about you?

313
00:17:56,325 --> 00:17:58,119
How much debt did you end up with?

314
00:17:58,202 --> 00:17:59,745
10 billion won?

315
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:03,040
That's why you're still in this.
Ever since you were a patrol cop,

316
00:18:03,124 --> 00:18:05,001
you've been cleaning up shit
that Geumseong leaves for you, right?

317
00:18:05,084 --> 00:18:07,044
I paid them all back already.

318
00:18:07,670 --> 00:18:09,171
Oh, is that so?

319
00:18:09,255 --> 00:18:12,049
Well, if you're debt free then cleaning
up shit must be in your nature.

320
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:16,929
You know what?

321
00:18:19,765 --> 00:18:21,517
You're a little shit.

322
00:18:21,601 --> 00:18:23,102
Better watch your mouth.

323
00:18:25,354 --> 00:18:26,689
Actually...

324
00:18:28,691 --> 00:18:29,859
My wife is very sick.

325
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:34,071
That so?

326
00:18:37,158 --> 00:18:39,744
I'm going.
I don't want to see you again.

327
00:18:39,827 --> 00:18:41,746
Hey, hey, hey.

328
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:45,249
At least tell me what's
in there before you go. Yeah?

329
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:46,709
Whatever the hell it is,

330
00:18:46,792 --> 00:18:49,211
it's making the guys
at headquarters crazy.

331
00:18:49,295 --> 00:18:51,130
And yet Narcotics are being awfully quiet.

332
00:18:51,213 --> 00:18:52,673
So I guess it's not drugs.

333
00:18:52,757 --> 00:18:54,717
Park didn't tell you anything?

334
00:18:57,136 --> 00:18:58,387
Maybe he doesn't know.

335
00:18:58,471 --> 00:19:00,473
Then what is it?
Come on, just tell me.

336
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:02,308
Huh?

337
00:19:03,643 --> 00:19:07,021
We got the information from Interpol
and it's still under review.

338
00:19:07,104 --> 00:19:08,481
You cannot leak this.

339
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:10,274
All right, all right, prick.

340
00:19:14,236 --> 00:19:15,321
Gold bars.

341
00:19:18,115 --> 00:19:19,158
Gold bars?

342
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:23,663
There's a Cambodian
trading company funded

343
00:19:23,746 --> 00:19:25,456
by the drug cartel, Krom thom.

344
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:29,251
The word is that the chairman buried
a massive slush fund.

345
00:19:29,335 --> 00:19:31,504
Under the ground.
Like, actually buried it.

346
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:34,715
Not cash, but gold bars.

347
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:36,467
Ten tons worth.

348
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:39,387
Somehow all
this information got leaked.

349
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:40,971
And the government launched
a massive search

350
00:19:41,055 --> 00:19:42,807
and seizure for tax evasion.

351
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:46,435
So all those gold bars,
they quickly moved them overseas.

352
00:19:46,519 --> 00:19:48,813
One ton of 10-kilogram gold bars
per shipment,

353
00:19:48,896 --> 00:19:51,148
disguised as caskets. However...

354
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:53,776
...one was found
at the airport in Hong Kong.

355
00:19:54,360 --> 00:19:56,153
And apparently another one is in Korea.

356
00:19:56,237 --> 00:19:58,155
And that's the casket, huh?

357
00:19:58,239 --> 00:20:00,282
-The one with a ton of gold?
-Yeah, probably.

358
00:20:02,326 --> 00:20:03,411
And besides,

359
00:20:03,494 --> 00:20:06,330
that's the only casket that's come in
from Cambodia recently.

360
00:20:41,574 --> 00:20:45,035
SEONGOGAE REST AREA

361
00:20:58,841 --> 00:21:01,677
-Is anybody here?
-Hi, there.

362
00:21:01,761 --> 00:21:03,846
-Yes, hello.
-Ah, yes.

363
00:21:03,929 --> 00:21:06,932
Excuse me,
but the surveillance camera outside,

364
00:21:07,016 --> 00:21:08,184
did you install it?

365
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:10,394
Yes.

366
00:21:10,478 --> 00:21:12,104
Well, I'm with the police. Here.

367
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:13,522
I'm Detective Kim Jinman.

368
00:21:13,606 --> 00:21:16,859
I reported the installation of that camera
to the police already.

369
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:18,152
Might there be an issue?

370
00:21:18,235 --> 00:21:20,029
Oh, no, no.
It's nothing like that.

371
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:22,531
There was a traffic accident out front
a few days ago.

372
00:21:22,615 --> 00:21:24,575
-I just want to check something out. Yeah.
-I see.

373
00:21:35,169 --> 00:21:36,420
GANGWON CENTRAL POLICE AGENCY
TRAFFIC INFORMATION CENTER

374
00:21:36,504 --> 00:21:37,797
-One moment. I'll take a look.
-Yeah.

375
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:39,757
Okay.

376
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:42,968
12:29 A.M.
Jingogae Intersection.

377
00:21:43,052 --> 00:21:46,764
And at 12:57 A.M.,
21 Jinbu Street.

378
00:21:46,847 --> 00:21:50,851
Next, at 1:32 A.M.
National Route 59.

379
00:21:50,935 --> 00:21:52,353
And at 1:55 A.M.,

380
00:21:52,436 --> 00:21:54,021
crossing Jeongsan Bridge.

381
00:21:54,939 --> 00:21:56,023
Jeongsan?

382
00:21:57,107 --> 00:21:58,317
Yes.

383
00:21:59,401 --> 00:22:00,861
GEUMSEONG TOURIST HOTEL

384
00:22:08,369 --> 00:22:09,620
Stop it.

385
00:22:09,703 --> 00:22:12,498
Ah, honey, it's fine.

386
00:22:12,581 --> 00:22:14,875
Wow, what's up with your hands?

387
00:22:14,959 --> 00:22:16,418
They're so pretty for a man.

388
00:22:16,502 --> 00:22:18,003
Because they're woman's hands.

389
00:22:18,087 --> 00:22:19,922
That means it's fine if I touch you,
right?

390
00:22:20,005 --> 00:22:21,465
Just kidding!

391
00:22:25,469 --> 00:22:26,929
Park Hocheol's here!

392
00:22:28,931 --> 00:22:29,849
CANCEL

393
00:22:29,932 --> 00:22:30,933
-Hey.
-What?

394
00:22:31,016 --> 00:22:32,560
-I finally found my love today!
-Get him outta here.

395
00:22:32,643 --> 00:22:34,270
-It's no fair!
-I know, I know.

396
00:22:34,353 --> 00:22:35,604
Oh, honey.

397
00:22:35,688 --> 00:22:38,315
You know, right?
My love?

398
00:22:38,399 --> 00:22:40,818
Honey, I have to be really honest
with you.

399
00:22:40,901 --> 00:22:42,486
Jeongah.

400
00:22:42,570 --> 00:22:43,779
Sorry!

401
00:22:44,655 --> 00:22:46,240
Oh, look.
Park has arrived.

402
00:22:46,323 --> 00:22:48,659
Right when we're getting
this party started.

403
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:52,204
I'm taking two of those girls out with me.

404
00:22:52,288 --> 00:22:54,999
-Have you found anything?
-Of course I did!

405
00:22:55,082 --> 00:22:56,584
Wait, what did I...

406
00:22:57,501 --> 00:22:59,003
You talkin' about the van?

407
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:01,630
Yeah, I've been looking around for it.

408
00:23:01,714 --> 00:23:04,091
I combed through the surveillance cameras
in Gangwon-do.

409
00:23:04,174 --> 00:23:05,509
I checked every single one.

410
00:23:05,593 --> 00:23:07,136
Quit rambling and just spit it out.

411
00:23:08,721 --> 00:23:09,722
Hey.

412
00:23:09,805 --> 00:23:11,891
I'm taking two of them today.

413
00:23:12,433 --> 00:23:14,018
-Yes, sir.
-Yeah? You got it?

414
00:23:14,101 --> 00:23:15,144
-Huh?
-Hey.

415
00:23:15,227 --> 00:23:16,729
-Move it.
-Yeah.

416
00:23:16,812 --> 00:23:18,606
Yeah, go get-
what are you doing?

417
00:23:18,689 --> 00:23:21,025
Go. Get them ready.
Good.

418
00:23:22,359 --> 00:23:23,777
Ah.

419
00:23:23,861 --> 00:23:25,446
What was I saying?

420
00:23:26,614 --> 00:23:28,073
Oh, right. The van.

421
00:23:28,991 --> 00:23:33,287
Was last seen here in Jeongsan.
Where we are.

422
00:23:33,370 --> 00:23:36,123
It was caught
on surveillance cameras.

423
00:23:36,206 --> 00:23:39,460
It shows up at the entrance
to Jeongsan Bridge.

424
00:23:39,543 --> 00:23:40,961
Then no trace of it anywhere.

425
00:23:41,045 --> 00:23:42,421
And two days later,

426
00:23:42,504 --> 00:23:45,633
they dump the van
at the abandoned warehouse,

427
00:23:45,716 --> 00:23:47,176
but it was empty.

428
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:50,804
So where did they hide
the casket? Huh?

429
00:23:52,389 --> 00:23:54,141
Right here.

430
00:23:54,224 --> 00:23:55,768
Jeongsan.

431
00:23:55,851 --> 00:23:57,978
They hid it here.

432
00:23:58,062 --> 00:24:00,648
So who was it, then?
The prick who was driving it?

433
00:24:00,731 --> 00:24:02,524
Oh, I don't really know about that.

434
00:24:02,608 --> 00:24:06,487
But either way, I've really
helped you narrow it down.

435
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:09,698
Just find out who was in Jeongsan that day
and catch 'em.

436
00:24:10,699 --> 00:24:11,700
Wouldn't that work?

437
00:24:11,784 --> 00:24:12,785
Find out quickly.

438
00:24:14,578 --> 00:24:17,414
Right, but I think I got a hold
of some info that you're gonna wanna hear.

439
00:24:18,207 --> 00:24:19,875
Yeah. You should know.

440
00:24:19,959 --> 00:24:21,877
-Yeah?
-What?

441
00:24:21,961 --> 00:24:24,880
I'm guessing you don't know what's in
that casket, do you?

442
00:24:24,964 --> 00:24:26,006
Well?

443
00:24:29,093 --> 00:24:31,553
You don't know, huh?
Well, I do.

444
00:24:36,225 --> 00:24:37,768
What's in it?

445
00:24:37,851 --> 00:24:40,938
Well, this info's worth
at least 100 gold chips.

446
00:24:41,021 --> 00:24:42,606
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
We can do that.

447
00:24:44,817 --> 00:24:46,652
Gold bars.

448
00:24:48,654 --> 00:24:50,280
A ton of them.

449
00:24:51,115 --> 00:24:52,449
One ton.

450
00:24:53,367 --> 00:24:54,618
The current market value...

451
00:24:56,245 --> 00:24:57,621
150 billion.

452
00:24:57,705 --> 00:24:59,498
Crazy, right?

453
00:25:00,582 --> 00:25:03,377
But then again,
you know what's really crazy?

454
00:25:03,460 --> 00:25:09,299
Is that, well, the chairman didn't
tell you you'd be smuggling gold, huh?

455
00:25:09,383 --> 00:25:10,801
Why is that?

456
00:25:11,552 --> 00:25:13,929
Seems like the kind of important stuff
you should know.

457
00:25:16,306 --> 00:25:18,892
I mean,
you are his right-hand man.

458
00:25:18,976 --> 00:25:20,686
Does that mean...

459
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:22,604
...is he demoting you?

460
00:25:24,356 --> 00:25:26,400
Guess it doesn't matter.

461
00:25:27,151 --> 00:25:28,610
As long as you get the job done.

462
00:25:34,283 --> 00:25:36,410
Yeah. So.

463
00:25:36,493 --> 00:25:39,038
I heard that you're one
of the best goldsmiths in the area.

464
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:43,167
Uh, yes, well...

465
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:45,627
-You've manufactured gold bars yourself?
-Yes.

466
00:25:45,711 --> 00:25:48,047
I need you to make ten bars.

467
00:25:48,130 --> 00:25:50,299
One kilo each, just like
I said on the phone.

468
00:25:50,382 --> 00:25:52,051
And of course we'll provide the gold.

469
00:25:53,093 --> 00:25:54,219
And your casting fee?

470
00:25:54,303 --> 00:25:55,429
Mm...

471
00:25:57,598 --> 00:25:58,807
One percent of cost.

472
00:25:58,891 --> 00:26:00,893
Pretty good, right?

473
00:26:00,976 --> 00:26:03,145
It's not every day you get
an offer like this.

474
00:26:04,396 --> 00:26:06,857
I'm curious,
how long will it take to make them?

475
00:26:07,816 --> 00:26:09,443
Around two to three days.

476
00:26:09,526 --> 00:26:11,236
-Two to three.
-You see,

477
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:12,196
gold bars don't require...

478
00:26:14,948 --> 00:26:16,658
Detailed craftsmanship.

479
00:26:17,242 --> 00:26:18,243
One thing, though.

480
00:26:18,327 --> 00:26:20,788
Where in Jeongsan are you from, exactly?

481
00:26:21,705 --> 00:26:23,707
Don't you have a business card?

482
00:26:23,791 --> 00:26:25,584
It's just that normally gold bars

483
00:26:25,667 --> 00:26:28,462
are manufactured
in specific authorized factories,

484
00:26:28,545 --> 00:26:29,755
so why don't you go to those?

485
00:26:29,838 --> 00:26:31,298
The thing is...

486
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:34,843
There's a reason why I'm paying you such
a high fee.

487
00:26:36,220 --> 00:26:37,554
It comes with one condition.

488
00:26:38,597 --> 00:26:39,807
What condition, you ask?

489
00:26:39,890 --> 00:26:41,308
No questions.

490
00:26:41,391 --> 00:26:44,686
The who, what, why, where,
none of it.

491
00:26:44,770 --> 00:26:46,814
They say silence is golden, right?

492
00:26:46,897 --> 00:26:50,818
So stay silent
and you can call it a golden fee.

493
00:26:50,901 --> 00:26:52,528
A golden fee?

494
00:26:52,611 --> 00:26:53,862
Yeah, that's right.

495
00:26:53,946 --> 00:26:55,697
And there's a second condition.

496
00:26:55,781 --> 00:26:57,074
It's not just questions.

497
00:26:57,157 --> 00:26:58,659
You can't say anything.

498
00:26:58,742 --> 00:26:59,743
You can't go around saying,

499
00:26:59,827 --> 00:27:02,496
"Hey, I'm working on this gold job.
They're 10-kilo bars,"

500
00:27:02,579 --> 00:27:04,456
to literally anyone.
If you do,

501
00:27:04,540 --> 00:27:06,041
our contract is over.

502
00:27:06,125 --> 00:27:08,836
Not only that,
your life will be over.

503
00:27:08,919 --> 00:27:10,254
Then you bought them illegally.

504
00:27:11,255 --> 00:27:12,548
If I refuse now...

505
00:27:13,465 --> 00:27:14,925
...I'll be okay, right?

506
00:27:18,095 --> 00:27:19,388
Of course.

507
00:27:19,471 --> 00:27:23,392
Mm, it's not like you saw
the gold or anything.

508
00:27:23,475 --> 00:27:25,060
So yeah,
if you don't wanna do it,

509
00:27:25,143 --> 00:27:27,271
no biggie.
It's not like anyone saw us here.

510
00:27:27,354 --> 00:27:31,775
No one knows that we met to talk and-
two percent, okay?

511
00:27:33,277 --> 00:27:34,486
3K per kilo.

512
00:27:35,362 --> 00:27:37,447
300 million for ten bars.

513
00:27:37,531 --> 00:27:39,032
Do you know anyone
who makes that in a month?

514
00:27:39,950 --> 00:27:42,244
I wouldn't offer this to anybody else,
Hoonseok.

515
00:27:42,327 --> 00:27:44,204
I like your face.

516
00:27:44,288 --> 00:27:47,457
You look like the type of guy
who'd make gold bars with total precision.

517
00:27:47,541 --> 00:27:49,126
I really want to work with you, okay?

518
00:27:51,211 --> 00:27:52,796
But if you'd rather refuse, say so, hmm?

519
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:54,840
I'm a busy man.
I have to go look for someone else now.

520
00:27:54,923 --> 00:27:57,593
-We're done here.
-The gold bar.

521
00:27:58,635 --> 00:28:01,096
Show me.
Then I'll decide.

522
00:28:03,348 --> 00:28:04,349
Okay.

523
00:28:09,938 --> 00:28:12,566
Here. This is it.

524
00:28:12,649 --> 00:28:13,775
Okay.

525
00:28:21,241 --> 00:28:22,826
Here he is.

526
00:28:22,910 --> 00:28:24,286
Mr. Lee Hoonseok.

527
00:28:25,787 --> 00:28:27,039
Yeah.

528
00:28:27,122 --> 00:28:28,916
And this is, uh...

529
00:28:30,042 --> 00:28:31,126
Call her Boss.

530
00:28:32,544 --> 00:28:34,963
Nice to meet you, Boss.

531
00:28:36,089 --> 00:28:37,466
Hello.

532
00:28:37,883 --> 00:28:39,134
He's going to work with us.

533
00:28:39,217 --> 00:28:40,552
He'll make the...

534
00:28:42,554 --> 00:28:44,306
You know what?
I've noticed your voice is kind of loud,

535
00:28:44,389 --> 00:28:46,475
so from now on we'll call
the gold bars "potatoes," okay?

536
00:28:47,225 --> 00:28:48,310
Show him the potato.

537
00:28:49,561 --> 00:28:51,229
He wants to check it.

538
00:28:54,775 --> 00:28:56,318
Hey, it's okay.
You're good to show him.

539
00:28:58,028 --> 00:28:59,655
We're all in the same boat now
so it's cool.

540
00:29:09,706 --> 00:29:11,249
Here.

541
00:29:32,729 --> 00:29:34,523
This is real.

542
00:29:35,899 --> 00:29:37,901
Well, of course it is.
It's the real deal.

543
00:29:40,153 --> 00:29:41,655
All right, I'll have it done.

544
00:29:41,738 --> 00:29:43,448
It won't take long.
Come back tomorrow night.

545
00:29:43,532 --> 00:29:45,033
Uh, no, no, no.

546
00:29:46,493 --> 00:29:47,494
It'd be better...

547
00:29:49,663 --> 00:29:50,831
...if you could start work today.

548
00:29:50,914 --> 00:29:52,416
And I would like to supervise.

549
00:29:52,499 --> 00:29:55,293
That's right. And while she's watching,
I'll also be watching.

550
00:29:56,837 --> 00:29:58,380
I can't do it right away.

551
00:29:58,463 --> 00:30:01,216
I need to get things like
a new crucible and new molds,

552
00:30:01,299 --> 00:30:02,718
and if we're stamping
the Korea Mint mark...

553
00:30:02,801 --> 00:30:03,844
I can wait.

554
00:30:04,761 --> 00:30:06,471
Yeah, yeah.
We can wait.

555
00:30:06,555 --> 00:30:09,016
Hey, you can understand
why she's suspicious.

556
00:30:09,099 --> 00:30:10,976
You can get all those things today, right?

557
00:30:11,059 --> 00:30:13,103
Then we can get started tonight, huh?

558
00:30:13,186 --> 00:30:14,312
Pull an all-nighter?

559
00:30:16,648 --> 00:30:17,983
How about this?

560
00:30:19,234 --> 00:30:20,360
Midnight tonight.

561
00:30:21,278 --> 00:30:22,863
Come to the front of the workshop.

562
00:30:24,823 --> 00:30:26,283
When everything's all set,
I'll give you guys a call.

563
00:30:26,366 --> 00:30:27,743
-And I'll let you inside.
-Nice.

564
00:30:27,826 --> 00:30:29,036
All right.

565
00:30:29,119 --> 00:30:30,120
So I'll call you later.

566
00:30:31,913 --> 00:30:33,623
-See you at midnight.
-Mm-hmm.

567
00:30:33,707 --> 00:30:35,667
Call us. Call us later.

568
00:30:41,673 --> 00:30:42,883
See?

569
00:30:42,966 --> 00:30:44,301
What'd I say?

570
00:30:44,384 --> 00:30:46,011
There's nothing money can't buy.

571
00:30:46,094 --> 00:30:49,181
Do you really think he's the right guy?

572
00:30:49,264 --> 00:30:50,599
He seems too nice.

573
00:30:51,892 --> 00:30:53,143
So? What's wrong with being a nice guy?

574
00:30:53,226 --> 00:30:54,478
He could have a sudden change
of heart

575
00:30:54,561 --> 00:30:57,522
and decide to report us to the police.

576
00:30:57,606 --> 00:30:59,066
Stop worrying about that.

577
00:30:59,149 --> 00:31:01,026
I told you I did
a background check on the guy.

578
00:31:01,943 --> 00:31:03,278
That guy there?

579
00:31:04,196 --> 00:31:06,198
He lives with his widowed mother
and sister.

580
00:31:06,281 --> 00:31:08,158
He's the breadwinner of the family.

581
00:31:08,241 --> 00:31:09,493
So what?

582
00:31:10,619 --> 00:31:11,953
Heeju.

583
00:31:12,788 --> 00:31:15,123
This is how we make deals in my world,
okay?

584
00:31:15,207 --> 00:31:17,125
Money's important
but collateral's necessary.

585
00:31:17,209 --> 00:31:18,502
It's absolutely essential.

586
00:31:18,585 --> 00:31:21,046
Last thing you want
is to get stabbed in the back.

587
00:31:21,129 --> 00:31:23,381
So you always have to consider
the worst-case scenario.

588
00:31:23,465 --> 00:31:24,883
And these guys?

589
00:31:24,966 --> 00:31:27,928
What's the one thing that keeps them
from doing something stupid or crazy?

590
00:31:28,011 --> 00:31:29,763
Collateral, of course.

591
00:31:29,846 --> 00:31:31,389
The more important the collateral is,

592
00:31:31,473 --> 00:31:33,183
the less likely they are
to screw us over.

593
00:31:34,643 --> 00:31:35,894
So you're saying...

594
00:31:37,062 --> 00:31:40,398
...his mom and younger sister
are collateral?

595
00:31:43,110 --> 00:31:45,821
-Ah, come on. You know what I mean.
-Then what's my collateral?

596
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:47,364
Is it my aunt?

597
00:31:49,449 --> 00:31:50,450
Heeju.

598
00:31:50,534 --> 00:31:51,910
That's why you went to the pawn shop
the other day.

599
00:31:51,993 --> 00:31:53,370
To check on my collateral?

600
00:31:53,453 --> 00:31:55,122
Are you seriously asking me that?

601
00:31:55,205 --> 00:31:56,790
I went because I wanted to see Auntie.

602
00:31:56,873 --> 00:31:59,584
You got it all wrong.
It's not like that.

603
00:31:59,668 --> 00:32:00,961
Ah, come on.

604
00:32:01,044 --> 00:32:02,337
Collateral's insane.

605
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:04,464
How 'bout we go eat?
What do you want?

606
00:32:06,007 --> 00:32:07,259
Bokjiri sounds good..

607
00:32:13,098 --> 00:32:14,349
Something's wrong.

608
00:32:15,642 --> 00:32:16,810
Give him a call.

609
00:32:16,893 --> 00:32:18,186
Well, he said he'd call
when he's ready.

610
00:32:23,316 --> 00:32:24,317
Yeah?

611
00:32:25,694 --> 00:32:26,736
Mm, okay.

612
00:32:59,895 --> 00:33:02,480
JEIL WORKSHOP

613
00:33:21,875 --> 00:33:23,210
Oh, here.

614
00:33:23,293 --> 00:33:24,419
Oh.

615
00:33:32,928 --> 00:33:34,763
I got it.

616
00:33:34,846 --> 00:33:36,014
Here.

617
00:33:43,271 --> 00:33:44,814
How long will it take?

618
00:33:44,898 --> 00:33:47,400
I'll be done with it before morning.

619
00:33:47,484 --> 00:33:50,278
I guess you two just wait here.

620
00:33:52,113 --> 00:33:55,116
Yeah, and don't you even think
about pulling any stunts.

621
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:56,993
I'll be watching you.

622
00:33:58,119 --> 00:33:59,871
I'm watching you over there, too!

623
00:35:10,025 --> 00:35:13,570
INCOMING CALL
JEIL WORKSHOP PRESIDENT NOH

624
00:35:13,653 --> 00:35:16,656
JEWELRY ECONOMY DAILY

625
00:35:21,328 --> 00:35:22,454
That's right.

626
00:35:27,626 --> 00:35:29,753
You went into that coal mine.

627
00:35:34,466 --> 00:35:35,925
DAD! BE SAFE AGAIN TODAY

628
00:35:48,813 --> 00:35:50,023
You were there?

629
00:35:50,982 --> 00:35:53,652
Of course I was.

630
00:36:00,408 --> 00:36:01,534
What was the name of that mutt, again?

631
00:36:02,994 --> 00:36:04,746
Mongsil or something.

632
00:36:05,955 --> 00:36:07,248
Don't you remember?

633
00:36:07,332 --> 00:36:09,125
You went in there while we
were playing freeze tag, I think.

634
00:36:11,211 --> 00:36:12,837
You were looking
for that stupid dog

635
00:36:12,921 --> 00:36:14,589
and I waited for you forever.

636
00:36:16,049 --> 00:36:18,343
I kept waiting,
but you didn't come out.

637
00:36:18,426 --> 00:36:20,762
So I went to get the Aunties.

638
00:36:23,014 --> 00:36:25,016
Mongsil, wait!

639
00:36:26,976 --> 00:36:28,436
Mongsil!

640
00:36:32,941 --> 00:36:34,192
Mongsil!

641
00:36:37,028 --> 00:36:38,863
Mongsil, here!

642
00:36:48,206 --> 00:36:49,541
Mongsil!

643
00:36:52,669 --> 00:36:53,878
Heeju.

644
00:36:56,214 --> 00:36:57,298
You don't remember?

645
00:37:00,468 --> 00:37:03,471
I'm not sure.
I don't think so.

646
00:37:05,557 --> 00:37:07,267
You really forgot.

647
00:37:08,351 --> 00:37:10,603
Come on.
You gotta remember.

648
00:37:10,687 --> 00:37:12,897
I practically saved your life, you know?

649
00:37:13,773 --> 00:37:14,774
I don't know.

650
00:37:14,858 --> 00:37:16,359
I seriously don't remember.

651
00:37:50,477 --> 00:37:52,228
Hoonseok?

652
00:37:54,189 --> 00:37:56,524
-Shh, quiet. Quiet.
-Are you there?

653
00:37:57,358 --> 00:37:58,359
Who is it?

654
00:37:59,736 --> 00:38:01,154
Hey! What are you doing?

655
00:38:01,237 --> 00:38:03,740
It's-it's the owner.

656
00:38:05,533 --> 00:38:06,701
Hold on.

657
00:38:09,871 --> 00:38:11,206
Hoonseok!

658
00:38:13,082 --> 00:38:14,292
Quick, come on.

659
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:15,794
-Come on.
-Are you asleep?

660
00:38:20,507 --> 00:38:22,133
Hoonseok.

661
00:38:25,470 --> 00:38:26,763
Ah, goodness.

662
00:38:26,846 --> 00:38:28,973
So you were in here.

663
00:38:29,057 --> 00:38:30,391
Yes. What are you...

664
00:38:30,475 --> 00:38:32,519
Well, why did you lock the door?

665
00:38:32,602 --> 00:38:34,479
What are you doing up at this hour?

666
00:38:36,940 --> 00:38:38,608
Uh, sir, can I talk to you for a sec?

667
00:38:40,610 --> 00:38:41,611
Hold on.

668
00:38:44,113 --> 00:38:47,033
There's nothing...

669
00:38:48,618 --> 00:38:49,661
Sir?

670
00:38:51,996 --> 00:38:53,665
Wait.

671
00:38:53,748 --> 00:38:55,750
What-what's all that?

672
00:38:58,795 --> 00:39:00,964
Spit it out!

673
00:39:01,047 --> 00:39:02,340
What are you up to?

674
00:39:03,341 --> 00:39:05,802
Someone from Janggak asked me
to do some craft work.

675
00:39:05,885 --> 00:39:07,262
Let go.

676
00:39:08,429 --> 00:39:10,682
What? Seems like a lot.

677
00:39:10,765 --> 00:39:13,601
It's 14k.
There's not much gold in it.

678
00:39:14,978 --> 00:39:16,145
Hold on, sir!

679
00:39:16,229 --> 00:39:17,105
Why do you wanna go in there?

680
00:39:17,188 --> 00:39:19,399
There's nothing to...

681
00:39:19,482 --> 00:39:20,817
Goodness, what's with you?

682
00:39:26,364 --> 00:39:27,907
What are you doing at this hour?

683
00:39:27,991 --> 00:39:29,200
Why aren't you at home sleeping?

684
00:39:34,289 --> 00:39:35,707
I couldn't sleep.

685
00:39:39,043 --> 00:39:41,838
I decided to sell this factory
to President Choi.

686
00:39:42,797 --> 00:39:44,215
It's best you stop working here...

687
00:39:45,967 --> 00:39:47,343
...and look somewhere else.

688
00:39:47,427 --> 00:39:48,595
But sir...

689
00:39:49,596 --> 00:39:51,055
I'm very sorry.

690
00:39:51,764 --> 00:39:53,641
I wanted to help you send your sister
to college.

691
00:39:54,559 --> 00:39:56,644
And of course I wanted to help your mom.

692
00:39:56,728 --> 00:39:59,439
Make sure you could take care
of her while she's unwell.

693
00:40:00,148 --> 00:40:02,817
But there's just
no way I can hold on anymore.

694
00:40:04,819 --> 00:40:06,446
Forget about me.

695
00:40:06,529 --> 00:40:09,157
What are you going
to do about paying off your loan?

696
00:40:09,240 --> 00:40:12,243
I thought you said Mr. Choi's offer
wasn't that great.

697
00:40:12,327 --> 00:40:14,954
Look, I wasn't good enough.

698
00:40:15,038 --> 00:40:17,081
That's why I'm in debt.
What can you do?

699
00:40:17,165 --> 00:40:18,875
Okay.

700
00:40:20,376 --> 00:40:21,544
Be careful.

701
00:40:21,628 --> 00:40:24,547
I hear there are a lot
of thieves stealing gold dust.

702
00:40:25,256 --> 00:40:27,008
Better keep the doors locked up.

703
00:40:27,091 --> 00:40:28,343
Yeah.

704
00:40:28,426 --> 00:40:30,261
Thank you.

705
00:40:30,345 --> 00:40:32,722
You've always been a hard worker.

706
00:40:47,445 --> 00:40:49,113
Wait a minute.
What was that noise?

707
00:40:49,989 --> 00:40:52,283
Uh, what noise?
I didn't hear any noise.

708
00:40:52,367 --> 00:40:54,285
-What's wrong with you?
-Nothing.

709
00:40:54,369 --> 00:40:55,370
Get out of my way, kid!

710
00:40:55,453 --> 00:40:57,580
-What was that?
-That was nothing!

711
00:40:57,664 --> 00:40:59,958
-You should just go...
-I'm going in!

712
00:41:00,041 --> 00:41:02,377
Sir, wait, please!
Don't go in there!

713
00:41:09,550 --> 00:41:11,302
We're fucked.
We're so fucked.

714
00:41:11,386 --> 00:41:12,553
Sir, are you okay?

715
00:41:14,013 --> 00:41:16,099
Why'd you do that?

716
00:41:16,182 --> 00:41:18,685
Sir, are you okay?

717
00:41:20,019 --> 00:41:21,604
He needs to go to the hospital.

718
00:41:23,564 --> 00:41:25,400
We have to take him, okay?

719
00:41:27,235 --> 00:41:29,278
Woogy. Hey. Hey!

720
00:41:29,362 --> 00:41:30,613
What are you doing?

721
00:41:31,447 --> 00:41:32,448
We have no choice.

722
00:41:32,532 --> 00:41:33,992
He saw the gold bar
so I gotta finish him off.

723
00:41:34,075 --> 00:41:35,034
-No!
-Are you crazy?

724
00:41:35,118 --> 00:41:36,869
Let go.

725
00:41:36,953 --> 00:41:38,037
Let go!

726
00:41:38,121 --> 00:41:40,206
Wait! Wait a second!

727
00:41:40,289 --> 00:41:42,041
Just-just put that down, okay?

728
00:41:42,125 --> 00:41:43,751
If you don't wanna help,
get out of the way.

729
00:41:44,669 --> 00:41:46,462
-I gotta cut him into pieces.
-No! You can't do that, no!

730
00:41:46,546 --> 00:41:47,755
Cut him up?

731
00:41:47,839 --> 00:41:49,632
-He's alive still!
-Is he?

732
00:41:49,716 --> 00:41:51,509
I guess I just have to kill him, then!

733
00:41:51,592 --> 00:41:52,635
You want the gold?

734
00:41:52,719 --> 00:41:54,053
Then fucking move!

735
00:41:54,137 --> 00:41:55,722
-No, you can't! You can't!
-Get off!

736
00:41:55,805 --> 00:41:57,682
I can talk to him!

737
00:41:57,765 --> 00:41:59,392
I can say you were thieves!
He won't know about the gold!

738
00:41:59,475 --> 00:42:01,686
Yeah! L-let him take him
to the hospital.

739
00:42:01,769 --> 00:42:03,646
After that, we can let
Hoonseok take care of it.

740
00:42:03,730 --> 00:42:05,231
Enough. Move out of the way.

741
00:42:07,108 --> 00:42:10,111
If you kill my boss,
then you'll have to kill me, too!

742
00:42:10,194 --> 00:42:11,487
Or else I'll spill everything I know!

743
00:42:11,571 --> 00:42:13,364
If you do this,

744
00:42:13,448 --> 00:42:16,159
then you and I are through!
You gonna kill me as well?

745
00:42:18,828 --> 00:42:21,831
Woogy. Woogy, please.

746
00:42:23,249 --> 00:42:24,709
You always used to listen to me.

747
00:42:24,792 --> 00:42:26,669
When we were kids.

748
00:42:28,671 --> 00:42:29,672
At the coal mine.

749
00:42:29,756 --> 00:42:31,382
And I fell down.

750
00:42:32,175 --> 00:42:34,385
It was you who saved me, right?

751
00:42:37,138 --> 00:42:38,681
That's right.

752
00:42:39,599 --> 00:42:41,350
I remember.

753
00:42:41,434 --> 00:42:42,477
It's just...

754
00:42:44,353 --> 00:42:45,688
...I didn't wanna remember it.

755
00:42:53,654 --> 00:42:54,947
Fuck.

756
00:43:11,339 --> 00:43:13,800
-Whoa, no!
-Hey! What?

757
00:43:13,883 --> 00:43:15,009
We're taking him to the hospital, right?

758
00:43:15,843 --> 00:43:19,639
Wait, wait, wait!
Behind your back, you-you have a knife.

759
00:43:20,723 --> 00:43:22,725
Fuck.

760
00:43:31,943 --> 00:43:35,321
Ah, fuck these damn
conscientious assholes.

761
00:43:38,032 --> 00:43:39,492
Oh, what the fuck am I doing?

762
00:43:42,954 --> 00:43:44,163
Is this even right?

763
00:43:44,789 --> 00:43:48,626
Ah, what is this shit? Ah!

764
00:44:42,013 --> 00:44:43,806
Okay.

765
00:44:43,890 --> 00:44:46,726
If they're off by point-one gram,
there's no need to worry.

766
00:44:46,809 --> 00:44:51,022
That's within the normal weight range,
so you'll sell them without any issues.

767
00:44:51,105 --> 00:44:54,233
As for the leftover dust and fragments,
I'll keep them here,

768
00:44:54,317 --> 00:44:56,444
and I'll mix them in when I do
the next casting.

769
00:44:57,778 --> 00:44:59,488
Thank you so much.
You did good work.

770
00:45:00,573 --> 00:45:01,991
Nice work.

771
00:45:02,074 --> 00:45:03,784
I'll be back in three days, 'kay?

772
00:45:03,868 --> 00:45:05,286
And the cash?

773
00:45:06,078 --> 00:45:07,205
Didn't we tell you?

774
00:45:08,664 --> 00:45:09,665
You didn't tell him?

775
00:45:09,749 --> 00:45:11,209
What?

776
00:45:12,251 --> 00:45:13,961
Well, it's a deferred payment.

777
00:45:14,045 --> 00:45:15,671
I'll settle it in three days.

778
00:45:15,755 --> 00:45:17,173
Wait, wait, wait.
Wait a minute.

779
00:45:17,256 --> 00:45:18,382
Uh, deferred?

780
00:45:18,466 --> 00:45:20,301
Come on.

781
00:45:21,219 --> 00:45:22,386
Shit, you don't trust us?

782
00:45:22,470 --> 00:45:24,347
Of course I don't trust you!

783
00:45:24,430 --> 00:45:27,475
How do I know you two will actually
come back in three days?

784
00:45:27,558 --> 00:45:29,101
Well, what do you want?

785
00:45:29,185 --> 00:45:30,436
I don't have it!
I don't have the cash!

786
00:45:30,519 --> 00:45:33,731
Hold on. We-we agreed
to give you two percent, didn't we?

787
00:45:33,814 --> 00:45:34,982
Yeah.

788
00:45:36,692 --> 00:45:37,693
Well, this...

789
00:45:39,153 --> 00:45:41,239
...is worth 150 mil.

790
00:45:41,322 --> 00:45:43,241
Consider this half upfront.

791
00:45:43,324 --> 00:45:46,077
And you'll get the rest once
the job is done.

792
00:45:46,994 --> 00:45:47,995
Oh.

793
00:45:49,956 --> 00:45:53,167
Wow. You really scored.

794
00:45:53,918 --> 00:45:55,211
Lucky you.

795
00:45:55,920 --> 00:45:58,047
Give it to me.
I'll exchange it for you.

796
00:45:58,130 --> 00:46:01,175
No, thanks.
I can take care of it myself.

797
00:46:02,385 --> 00:46:05,846
And you'll promise us that you'll be able
to work on the rest, too?

798
00:46:07,098 --> 00:46:09,725
Yes, Boss.
I'll do it because I trust you.

799
00:46:11,727 --> 00:46:13,938
But I don't trust him at all.

800
00:46:14,021 --> 00:46:17,733
You motherfucker. You think you can point
your finger and say that shit to my face?

801
00:46:17,817 --> 00:46:19,277
Who the fuck do you think you are?

802
00:46:19,360 --> 00:46:20,444
-You wanna die?
-See you next time.

803
00:46:20,528 --> 00:46:22,280
What a piece of shit.
Hey, hey!

804
00:46:22,363 --> 00:46:24,156
I don't trust you either, you
prick!

805
00:46:24,240 --> 00:46:26,742
-Where's my knife? No!
-Stop it. Come on. Come on.

806
00:46:35,084 --> 00:46:36,085
Sorry.

807
00:46:37,211 --> 00:46:39,088
I got worked up earlier.

808
00:46:40,715 --> 00:46:43,050
The whole situation kinda got out
of control.

809
00:46:46,345 --> 00:46:47,596
Do you need a doctor?

810
00:46:48,472 --> 00:46:49,473
Forget it.

811
00:46:50,391 --> 00:46:52,435
Instead, I need your word.

812
00:46:53,269 --> 00:46:57,064
If you and I are going to work together,
you won't kill anyone.

813
00:46:57,148 --> 00:47:01,235
If you ever pull a knife
or spill blood one more time,

814
00:47:01,319 --> 00:47:03,112
you and I are done.
It's over.

815
00:47:07,366 --> 00:47:09,368
What if someone finds out
we're doing this?

816
00:47:14,332 --> 00:47:16,792
You think you're being
fucking conscientious?

817
00:47:16,876 --> 00:47:17,877
Hmm?

818
00:47:20,421 --> 00:47:22,256
That mindset doesn't make
any fucking sense

819
00:47:22,340 --> 00:47:23,466
for a wannabe thief.

820
00:47:24,383 --> 00:47:27,928
Fuck.
You're stealing gold, you know.

821
00:47:28,012 --> 00:47:30,556
A whopping 100 kilograms
of someone else's gold.

822
00:47:31,265 --> 00:47:34,477
And now you want the money?
All in good conscience?

823
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:36,395
Without getting blood
on your hands?

824
00:47:41,901 --> 00:47:43,611
Well, then.

825
00:47:43,694 --> 00:47:45,404
Do you promise or not?

826
00:47:48,741 --> 00:47:50,242
Yeah, I'll do my best.

827
00:47:59,168 --> 00:48:00,169
Here.

828
00:48:52,888 --> 00:48:54,515
How much longer
are you gonna sleep?

829
00:48:54,598 --> 00:48:56,434
It's already dark out.

830
00:48:57,476 --> 00:48:58,894
Keep still.

831
00:49:00,312 --> 00:49:01,313
Almost done.

832
00:49:15,911 --> 00:49:16,912
Go.

833
00:49:18,664 --> 00:49:20,040
Get out of here.

834
00:49:22,084 --> 00:49:23,335
Run away.

835
00:49:23,419 --> 00:49:25,254
I'll pay off all of your debt for you.

836
00:49:26,172 --> 00:49:28,757
Do you even have the money
to pay off my debt?

837
00:49:29,383 --> 00:49:30,593
You don't even know what I owe.

838
00:49:31,677 --> 00:49:33,137
How much is it?

839
00:49:36,182 --> 00:49:37,475
I don't have debt.

840
00:49:38,934 --> 00:49:41,020
When it's time, I'll leave quietly.
Don't worry.

841
00:49:42,021 --> 00:49:43,063
Where were you last night?

842
00:49:45,191 --> 00:49:46,817
Were you hanging out with that thug?

843
00:49:48,110 --> 00:49:50,154
-What on Earth did you do with your hand?
-I already told you,

844
00:49:50,237 --> 00:49:51,614
there's nothing going on!

845
00:49:52,990 --> 00:49:54,074
And my hand...

846
00:49:55,284 --> 00:49:56,744
I just fell, okay?

847
00:49:56,827 --> 00:49:58,787
Don't tell me it was from a fall!
It was from a knife.

848
00:49:58,871 --> 00:50:00,206
Enough, all right.

849
00:50:01,123 --> 00:50:03,667
Wow. You luckless bitch.

850
00:50:04,877 --> 00:50:06,962
You ran away and still ended up like this.

851
00:50:11,550 --> 00:50:13,594
You wanna know what's really ridiculous?

852
00:50:14,637 --> 00:50:18,516
Everyone can tell that the bitch
with the worst luck is you.

853
00:50:19,892 --> 00:50:22,603
So hearing you call me that
just makes me furious.

854
00:50:23,646 --> 00:50:25,231
It really pisses me off.

855
00:50:28,526 --> 00:50:30,528
Don't put all your trust
into men like that.

856
00:50:32,154 --> 00:50:34,073
One moment can ruin your whole life.

857
00:50:34,156 --> 00:50:35,574
You're one to talk.

858
00:50:35,658 --> 00:50:37,910
Then why did you marry that trash?

859
00:50:37,993 --> 00:50:39,620
To survive.

860
00:50:39,703 --> 00:50:42,122
You think I could pay off my debt
and raise a kid by serving coffee?

861
00:50:42,206 --> 00:50:44,416
-If it weren't for you I would've...
-Don't use me as an excuse!

862
00:50:44,500 --> 00:50:46,252
I never asked for any of that!

863
00:50:47,711 --> 00:50:49,964
Every single moment I had to spend
with that man was nothing but hell!

864
00:50:50,047 --> 00:50:51,131
An do you think I was happy?

865
00:50:51,215 --> 00:50:53,884
That's why I begged you to run away!

866
00:50:53,968 --> 00:50:55,219
You didn't wanna go, though!

867
00:50:55,302 --> 00:50:57,471
Even after I told you what
that man tried to do to me, you...

868
00:50:57,555 --> 00:50:59,723
What is the point
of dredging this up now?

869
00:50:59,807 --> 00:51:01,350
Should I beg for your forgiveness?

870
00:51:01,433 --> 00:51:02,977
-Would that make it better?
-Yes!

871
00:51:03,894 --> 00:51:05,396
Beg and apologize.

872
00:51:05,479 --> 00:51:07,064
So I can feel better.

873
00:51:51,567 --> 00:51:53,110
Heeju, Heeju.
Don't come out.

874
00:51:53,193 --> 00:51:54,612
Your uncle is here.

875
00:52:05,205 --> 00:52:07,291
Well? You glad to see me?

876
00:52:07,374 --> 00:52:08,792
It's been two months.

877
00:52:08,876 --> 00:52:12,254
Uh, I was about to close up here.

878
00:52:13,547 --> 00:52:15,841
Let's go home.
Did you eat?

879
00:52:21,764 --> 00:52:23,015
Get in here already.

880
00:52:26,226 --> 00:52:29,313
Hi. It's me again.

881
00:52:33,817 --> 00:52:37,738
So I heard you sold a watch
to Mr. Jang a week ago.

882
00:52:37,821 --> 00:52:39,615
For 30 million.

883
00:52:40,866 --> 00:52:42,868
How much did you pay for it?

884
00:52:43,786 --> 00:52:45,663
You were able to sell for a high price.

885
00:52:45,746 --> 00:52:47,289
And you didn't tell me.

886
00:52:49,291 --> 00:52:54,046
I mean, I thought the price was, well,
a little too high.

887
00:52:54,129 --> 00:52:55,631
So I let Han know.

888
00:52:56,715 --> 00:52:58,050
All right, bring me the ledger.

889
00:52:59,176 --> 00:53:02,179
I said bring me the ledger.

890
00:53:22,408 --> 00:53:24,076
What else did you say you took?

891
00:53:24,868 --> 00:53:27,371
That's all for this month.
Wait, actually,

892
00:53:27,454 --> 00:53:29,415
I bought a few rings, too.

893
00:53:29,498 --> 00:53:31,375
I think she priced those correctly.

894
00:53:33,794 --> 00:53:35,462
You said you got diamonds.

895
00:53:35,546 --> 00:53:37,756
'Bout a month ago.

896
00:53:43,011 --> 00:53:44,054
No diamonds.

897
00:53:45,097 --> 00:53:47,015
Not even one.

898
00:53:52,229 --> 00:53:54,648
Is there a separate ledger for Janggak?

899
00:54:05,033 --> 00:54:06,326
You can go home now.

900
00:54:09,121 --> 00:54:12,249
I hope I didn't say anything that
was unnecessary.

901
00:54:12,332 --> 00:54:14,418
No, you were right to.

902
00:54:14,501 --> 00:54:16,545
I'm the owner and the husband.

903
00:54:17,212 --> 00:54:19,047
-Best that I know everything.
-Right.

904
00:54:19,131 --> 00:54:21,216
All right, then.
Take care.

905
00:54:23,469 --> 00:54:25,012
Uh, I'll see you.

906
00:54:25,095 --> 00:54:26,221
Goodbye.

907
00:54:39,401 --> 00:54:41,570
You must
have really lost your mind.

908
00:54:45,115 --> 00:54:48,327
You were just a coffee shop girl
with a little kid.

909
00:54:48,410 --> 00:54:50,329
I took you in and fed you,

910
00:54:50,412 --> 00:54:52,956
and you thank me
by taking my money on the sly?

911
00:55:02,758 --> 00:55:04,134
When did this start?

912
00:55:06,261 --> 00:55:08,055
How much have you skimmed now?

913
00:55:10,933 --> 00:55:12,726
-That's all.
-Oh.

914
00:55:13,852 --> 00:55:15,521
Really?

915
00:55:17,356 --> 00:55:20,567
You thieving bitch.

916
00:55:21,318 --> 00:55:24,196
Look at you still lying through
your fucking teeth!

917
00:55:30,369 --> 00:55:31,411
Shit!

918
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:36,041
Where do you think you're going?

919
00:55:36,124 --> 00:55:37,543
Come here!

920
00:55:45,592 --> 00:55:47,719
Better not say you fucking spent it all.

921
00:55:47,803 --> 00:55:51,098
If you did, I swear I'll
send you straight to Heaven.

922
00:55:53,976 --> 00:55:54,977
I swear.

923
00:55:58,689 --> 00:56:00,315
Hah!

924
00:56:07,489 --> 00:56:08,657
You won't say?

925
00:56:08,740 --> 00:56:11,827
You know I won't hesitate
to cut you.

926
00:56:11,910 --> 00:56:13,912
I am gonna check the ledgers.

927
00:56:13,996 --> 00:56:16,999
So why don't you just spit it out,
fucking bitch?

928
00:56:26,383 --> 00:56:29,928
No, Heeju!
No, don't do it.

929
00:56:42,316 --> 00:56:45,152
Go.
Hurry, hurry, go.

930
00:56:45,235 --> 00:56:47,070
Look at me and get a hold of yourself!

931
00:56:47,154 --> 00:56:49,114
Just grab what you need and go.

932
00:56:49,197 --> 00:56:50,449
I'll take care of everything.

933
00:57:13,180 --> 00:57:15,432
Take this.
It's the money I've earned over the years.

934
00:57:16,475 --> 00:57:17,809
I've been saving it for you.

935
00:57:19,978 --> 00:57:22,439
So take it and don't ever come back.

936
00:57:22,522 --> 00:57:26,360
No matter what happens to me,
don't try to look for me.

937
00:57:26,443 --> 00:57:27,444
Don't try to find out.

938
00:57:28,445 --> 00:57:29,821
You go somewhere far away.

939
00:57:30,864 --> 00:57:32,491
I want you to live a good life.

940
00:57:33,492 --> 00:57:34,493
No.

941
00:57:35,786 --> 00:57:37,746
You have to go.

942
00:57:37,829 --> 00:57:40,457
I'm really sorry.
Heeju.

943
00:57:40,540 --> 00:57:42,584
I'm sorry.

944
00:57:42,668 --> 00:57:45,212
I need you to listen.
Just listen to me this once.

945
00:57:45,295 --> 00:57:47,339
Go! You going will save my life.

946
00:57:47,422 --> 00:57:49,716
Go. Go!

947
00:57:49,800 --> 00:57:51,718
Auntie! Auntie!

948
00:57:51,802 --> 00:57:52,803
-Go!
-Auntie!

949
00:57:54,971 --> 00:57:58,392
I told you to go! Go!
Hurry up and get outta here!

950
00:58:00,268 --> 00:58:02,729
I said go away! Go!

951
00:58:39,141 --> 00:58:40,142
Hello.

952
00:58:40,684 --> 00:58:43,729
I-I'm in Bukju.

953
00:58:45,439 --> 00:58:47,399
The Happy Pawnshop in Bukju.

954
00:58:48,734 --> 00:58:52,571
I think I killed a person.

955
00:59:35,989 --> 00:59:37,199
Auntie.

956
00:59:39,618 --> 00:59:40,744
Mom.
